  "prompt": "How do you cut a granite countertop?",
  "response": "Cutting a granite countertop requires specialized tools and skills. Here's a general process:\n\n1. Tools needed:\n- Circular saw with diamond blade\n- Wet saw\n- Angle grinder\n- Safety glasses\n- Dust mask\n- Work gloves\n- Measuring tape\n- Straight edge or guide\n- Masking tape\n\n2. Preparation steps:\n- Measure and mark cut lines carefully\n- Use masking tape along cut line to reduce chipping\n- Ensure work area is well-ventilated\n- Wear proper safety equipment\n\n3. Cutting techniques:\n- Use a wet saw for most cuts\n- Cut slowly and steadily\n- Keep blade cool with water\n- Support the granite to prevent cracking\n- Make multiple shallow passes instead of one deep cut\n\n4. For sink or cooktop cutouts:\n- Use a template\n- Drill starter holes\n- Use a specialized hole saw or angle grinder\n\n5. Professional considerations:\n- Complex cuts are best done by professionals\n- Granite is heavy and fragile\n- Improper cutting can cause expensive damage\n\nRecommended for most people: Hire a professional fabricator for precise, safe granite cutting.",
